It looks like JB already covered a number of issues, so I&#39;ll just say that =
I have taught Java to some folks here at work during a regular lunchtime se=
ssion, and we did everything test first. These were COBOL programmers tryin=
g to bring their resumes up-to-date and they had no problem with the concep=
t of test-driven development.

Although, funnily enough, one just asked me =
the other day: &quot;so, how do you run code after you&#39;ve tested it?&quot; Oops, I gu=
ess you can overdo the emphasis on testing! :-) Needless to say, we had a q=
uick lesson on the joys of the main() method and actually running code from=
 a commandline rather than a test harness.

As an aside, for non-trivial cu=
rrency transactions, a dedicated money object that handles different curren=
cies would be a better bet than either longs or BigDecimals.

Simon

